value.value: A melanocyte that produces pigment within the hair follicle.
A melanocyte that produces pigment in the epithelium.

definition.value: The text defintion reference to the MP term appears to reference an epidermal melanocyte term. This term represents any melanocyte in any epithelium.

value.value: A melanocyte of the retina. This cell type is distinct from pigmented retinal epithelium.

A melanocyte located between the epithelial marginal cell layer and the mesodermal basal cell layer within the intrastrial space; the predominant cellular component of the electrogenic machinery that generates an endocochlear potential (80-100 mV) .
A neuronal receptor that respond to mechanical pressure or distortion in the skin.

A trophoblast cell that has a large volume of cytoplasm, is polyploid and is usually mononuclear but is also occasionally multi-nucleate. This cell type is important in establishing maternal physiology and remodeling of the vasculature of the placenta.
A thymocyte that lacks expression of CD4 and CD8.

definition.value: These are precursors to mature T cells; normally, they do not circulate, but are found in the thymus and they have not undergone rearrangement of the alpha and beta T cell receptor genes.

value.value: A supporting cell of the organ of Corti.
A specialized cell involved in auditory sensory perception.

A polarized columnar cell that covesr the lateral surface of the cochlear duct, secretes potassium ions and forms a continuous sheet in contact with the endolymph; marginal cells form extensive interdigitations with the basal and intermediate cells in the normal adult stria.
A polarized cell that is juxtaposed to fibrocytes in the underlying spiral ligament. This cell type secretes potassium ions derived from fibrocytes through gap junctions.

definition.value: Basal cells form a multi-layered epithelial barrier that separates the extracellular spaces of the stria vascularis and the spiral ligament[PMID:18353863]

value.value: A cell located in the heart, including both muscle and non muscle cells.

definition.value: From Onard of the FMA: Cardiac muscle cell or cardiac myocyte is a striated muscle cell. Cardiocyte on the other hand is any cell in the heart which includes cells other than muscle cells (e.g. endothelial cell of endocardium). Unless there is a consensus among anatomists that cardiocytes refer only to muscle cells, we will treat them as a general class of cells in the heart.

value.value: A fetal and neonatal heart cell that undergoes proliferation and is not yet terminally differentiated into a binucleate or a multinucleate cardiac myocyte.
A T cell that is located in the intestinal epithelium and is capable of a mucosal immune response.
A trophoblast giant cell derived from the mural trophectoderm.
A trophoblast giant cell that is derived from ectoplacental cone and, later in gestation, the spongiotrophoblast.
A trophoblast cell that arises in the junctional zone (basal plate) of the placenta.
A P/D1 enteroendocrine cell that is Grimelius positive and stores bombesin-like polypeptide.
A P/D1 enteroendocrine cell that is argyrophilic and stores vasoactive intestinal polypeptide.
An enteroendocrine cell of the small intestine that secretes motilin.
A cell of the adventitial layer of ductal structures such as the uterer, defent duct, biliary duct, etc
A smooth muscle cell of the intestine.
A CD11b-positive dendritic cell that is CD11b-high, CD45-positive, MHC-II-positive and CD103-negative.
A CD11b-positive dendritic cell that is CD11b-low, CD45-positive, MHC-II-high and CD103-positive that is located in the liver.
A dermal dendritic cell isolated from skin draining lymph nodes that is langerin-positive, MHC-II-positive, and CD4-negative and CD8a-negative.

label.value: langerin-negative, CD103-negative lymph node dendritic cell

value.value: A dermal dendritic cell isolated from skin draining lymph nodes that is langerin-negative, MHC-II-positive, and CD4-negative and CD8a-negative.

label.value: CD103-positive, langerin-positive lymph node dendritic cell

value.value: A langerin-positive lymph node dendritic cell that is CD103-positive and CD11b-low.

label.value: CD103-negative, langerin-positive lymph node dendritic cell

value.value: A langerin-positive lymph node dendritic cell that is CD103-negative and CD11b-high.

label.value: CD11b-low, CD103-negative, langerin-negative lymph node dendritic cell

value.value: A langerin-negative lymph node dendritic cell that is CD103-negative and CD11b-low.

label.value: CD11b-high, CD103-negative, langerin-negative lymph node dendritic cell

value.value: A langerin-negative lymph node dendritic cell that is CD103-negative and CD11b-high.

label.value: Vgamma5-positive CD8alpha alpha positive gamma-delta intraepithelial T cell

value.value: A CD8alpha alpha positive gamma-delta intraepithelial T cell that expresses a TCR encoded in part by the Vgamma5 gene segment.

label.value: Vgamma5-negative CD8alpha alpha positive gamma-delta intraepithelial T cell

value.value: A CD8alpha alpha positive gamma-delta intraepithelial T cell that does not express a TCR partially encoded by the Vgamma5 gene segment.
An interrenal chromaffin cell found in teleosts that contain heterogeneous vesicles with electron-dense granules located asymmetrically within the vesicular membrane.
A chromaffin cell interspersed among the interrenal epithelial layer of the anterior kidney of teloest fish.
An interrenal chromaffin cell found in teleosts that contain small, homogeneous electron-lucent granules that are separated from the vesicular membrane by a visible halo.
An epithelial cell of the kidney.

An interrenal epithelial kidney cell is an epithelial cell found in the anterior kidney of teleosts fish. This cell type is arranged in layers around the posterior cardinal vein and contains many mitochondria with tubulovesicular cristae. Interrenal chromaffin cells are interspersed among the tissue layer created by this cell type.
An insect excretory cell that regulates hemolymph composition by filtration and filtrate endocytosis.
A fat cell that is part of subcutaneous adipose tissue.
A renal filtration cell is a specialized cell of the renal system that filter fluids by charge, size or both.
A specialized epithelial cell that contains "feet" that interdigitate with the "feet" of other glomerular epithelial cells in the mesonephros.
A disseminated nephrocyte is a nephrocyte that filters hemolymph and is found at scattered locations in the fat body or other tissues.
A specialized epithelial cell that contains "feet" that interdigitate with the "feet" of other glomerular epithelial cells in the metanephros.
A dermal dendritic cell that is CD1a-negative and CD14-positive.

definition.value: They are also CD11c-positive, CD40-positive, CD85j-positive (ILT-2), CD163-positive, CD205-positive (DEC205), CD207-negative (langerin), CD209-positive (DC-SIGN), CD274-positive (PD-L1), CD324-negative (E-cadherin), Factor XIIIa-positive, LOX-I-positive, CLEC6-positive, Dectin-1-positive, and DCIR-positive. Upon stimulation, these cells are capable of producing IL1-beta, IL6, IL8, IL10, IL12p40, IL19, IL20, IL24, TGF-beta, TNF-alpha, GM-CSF, and MCP1. They reside in the dermis.

value.value: An immature CD14-positive dermal dendritic cell is CD80-low, CD86-low, and MHCII-low.
A mature CD14-positive dermal dendritic cell is CD80-high, CD86-high, MHCII-high and is CD83-positive.
A dermal dendritic cell that is CD1a-positive and CD14-negative.

definition.value: Reside in the dermis. They are also CD11c-positive, CD40-positive, CD207-negative (langerin), CD209-negative (DC-SIGN), and CD324-negative (E-cadherin). When activated, they are capable of producing CXCL8 (IL-8) and IL-15. Possibly a precursor of Langerhans cells or equivalent of langerin-positive dermal DCs in the mouse.

value.value: An immature CD1a-positive dermal dendritic cell is CD80-low, CD86-low, and MHCII-low.
A mature CD1a-positive dermal dendritic cell is CD80-high, CD83-positive, CD86-high, and MHCII-high.
A myeloid dendritic cell found in the blood that is CD16-positive.

definition.value: Normally represent 65-75% of peripheral blood mDCs (human). They are also CD281-positive (TLR1), CD282-positive (TLR2), CD284-positive (TLR4), CD285-positive (TLR5), CD286-positive (TLR6), CD288-positive (TLR8), CD289-positive (TLR9), and CD290-positive (TLR10) by RT-PCR [PMID:17332250]. Upon TLR stimulation, these cells are potent producers of TNF-alpha, while producing little CXCL8 (IL8).
